# What Is OOM Killer?

OOM Killer is:

> A Linux kernel mechanism that terminates processes when memory exhaustion threatens overall system stability.

It is a survival mechanism.

---

# The Golden Rule

> Linux prioritizes system survival over application survival.

Always.

---

# Memory Exhaustion Lifecycle

Linux does not immediately kill processes.

It escalates.

```text
Healthy

↓

Pressure

↓

Memory Reclaim

↓

Swap

↓

Heavy Pressure

↓

OOM Killer
```

