# OOM Score

View score:

```bash
cat /proc/PID/oom_score
```

Example:

```text
850
```

High risk.

---

# OOM Score Adjustment

View:

```bash
cat /proc/PID/oom_score_adj
```

Range:

```text
-1000

↓

1000
```

---

# Meaning

```text
-1000 = Never kill

0 = Default

1000 = Kill first
```

---

# Example

Protect PostgreSQL:

```bash
echo -1000 > /proc/PID/oom_score_adj
```

Dangerous if misused.

---

